PART VIII — THE SOVEREIGN DECLARATION
───────────────────────────────────────

We do not compete. We define the category.

Property management has been a human problem since 3000 BCE (Mesopotamian
clay tablet lease records). We are the first to make it a machine problem.

The machine never sleeps. The machine knows every jurisdiction.
The machine closes deals while the landlord is on holiday.
The machine files KES tax returns at midnight.
The machine generates AR walkthroughs without a photographer.

This is not disruption. This is replacement.

By 2028: $1.345B ARR. 52,400+ managers. 120 countries.
         The world's property managed by one Sovereign OS.

